        "content": "<p>The Ji Series uses Xinzuo’s proprietary <strong>12Cr18MoV steel</strong>, a composition not found in other knife brands. Learn how Damascus layering enhances blade performance. <a href=\"/blogs/news/damascus-pattern-performance-price-guide\">Damascus pattern guide</a></p><p>Wondering how 67-layer Damascus compares to 73-layer construction? We break down the differences in steel behaviour and visual pattern. <a href=\"/blogs/news/67-layer-vs-73-layer-damascus\">67 vs 73 layer Damascus compared</a></p><p>Keep your Ji Series looking and performing its best with proper care techniques for Damascus blades. <a href=\"/blogs/news/how-to-care-for-damascus-steel-knives\">Damascus knife care guide</a></p><p>Not sure if Damascus is worth the investment? Learn how to spot authentic Damascus construction. <a href=\"/blogs/news/real-damascus-steel-vs-fake\">Real vs fake Damascus steel</a></p><p>Understand how <strong>steel hardness</strong> at 59–61 HRC affects edge retention, sharpening, and everyday use. <a href=\"/blogs/news/knife-steel-hardness-guide\">Steel hardness guide</a></p><p>Looking for a 67-layer Damascus alternative with rosewood handles? The <strong>Yi Series</strong> offers a classic pairing. <a href=\"/collections/b27-yi-series\">Shop the Yi Series</a></p>",
